'''Olys Corellisi''',<ref name="By the Numbers">{{SWKidsYouTube|series=Star Wars By the Numbers|text=Every Language in Star Wars Movies|video=CZp8Civk2co|nolive=1}}</ref> translated to '''Old Corellian''', was an ancient [[Corellian]] [[language]]. In the [[Corellian Spike]] variation of the [[sabacc]] game, the two cards with a value of 0 were called ''[[sylop]]s'', which meant "idiots" in Old Corellian.<ref name="RT:RF" /> By the time of the [[New Republic]], a song in Old Corellian<ref name="Adelphi jukebox tweet">{{Twitter|pabl0hidalgo|status/1678184134798106625|Pablo Hidalgo|quote=This did not end up getting covered anywhere else, so it seems okay enough to share. The song on the Adelphi jukebox was written in English by the show staff and I translated it into Olys Corellisi — Old Corellian. It required a fair amount of invention but that was the intent.|archivedate=20230712085703}}</ref> was played in a [[The Pilots' Rest Quonset hut|lounge]] in [[Adelphi Base]], which was a [[New Republic]] outpost on [[Adelphi]].<ref name="Chapter 21">{{TheMandalorian|Chapter 21: The Pirate}}</ref>

